Can I verify the central limit theorem?

First with a for loop

output = vector("list", length = 100)

for (i in 1:100) {
  
  output[[i]] = sim_mean_sd(30)
  
}

output |> 
  bind_rows() |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = mu_hat)) +
  geom_density()

Try to repeat with a map statement

sim_results_df = 
  expand_grid(
    sample_size = c(30, 60, 90, 120), #iterations 1-100 for sample size 30, then 60, etc
    iter = 1:1000
  ) |> 
  mutate(
    results = map(sample_size, sim_mean_sd)
  ) |> 
  unnest(results)

Lets look at this:

sim_results_df |> 
  mutate(
    sample_size = str_c("n = ", sample_size),
    sample_size = fct_inorder(sample_size)
  ) |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_size, y = mu_hat)) +
  geom_violin()

Simple linear regression

sim_df = 
  tibble(
    x = rnorm(30, mean = 1, sd = 1),
    y = 2 + 3 * x + rnorm(30, 0, 1)
  )

sim_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y )) +
  geom_point()

slr_fit = lm(y ~ x, data = sim_df)

coef(slr_fit)
## (Intercept)           x 
##    2.174324    3.061644

Turn this into a function

sim_regression = function(n_subj, beta_0 = 2, beta_1 = 3) {
  
  sim_df = 
  tibble(
    x = rnorm(n_subj, mean = 1, sd = 1),
    y = beta_0 + beta_1 * x + rnorm(n_subj, 0, 1)
  )

  slr_fit = lm(y ~ x, data = sim_df)

  tibble(
    beta0_hat = coef(slr_fit)[1],
    beta1_hat = coef(slr_fit)[2]
  )
  
}
sim_regression(n_subj = 30)
## # A tibble: 1  2
##   beta0_hat beta1_hat
##       <dbl>     <dbl>
## 1      1.59      3.43
output = vector("list", length = 500)

One more example

birthdays = sample(1:365, 5, replace = TRUE)

repeated_bday = length(unique(birthdays)) < 5

repeated_bday
## [1] FALSE

Put this in a function

bday_sim = function(n_room) {
  
  birthdays = sample(1:365, n_room, replace = TRUE)

  repeated_bday = length(unique(birthdays)) < n_room
  
  repeated_bday
  
}

bday_sim(20)
## [1] TRUE
bday_sim_results = 
  expand_grid(
    bdays = 5:50,
    iter = 1:2500
  ) |> 
  mutate(
    result = map_lgl(bdays, bday_sim)
  ) |> 
  group_by(bdays) |> 
  summarize(
    prob_repeat = mean(result)
  )

Plot this

bday_sim_results |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = bdays, y = prob_repeat)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line()
